body:
I've been working on streaming and pipeline interruption lately. It was bothering me that checking ctrl+c (something we want to do often) always requires a bunch of boilerplate like:
```rust
use std::sync::atomic::Ordering;

if let Some(ctrlc) = &engine_state.ctrlc {
     if ctrlc.load(Ordering::SeqCst) {
          ...
```
I added a helper method to cut that down to:

```rust
if nu_utils::ctrl_c::was_pressed(&engine_state.ctrlc) {
    ...
```
